Applying %s. For the difference between mirror and mirror geometry, see help documentation.
Msg.ExtDesc:
This tool provides two types of mirror operations:
Mirror: This will mirror the object(s) in the x origin in the 2D plane. It will also mirror the object(s) in the z axis. For example, a symbol with pads on the TOP layer will, when mirrored, now have its pads on the BOTTOM layer.
Mirror Geometry: This will also mirror the objects in the x origin. However, it will NOT change any z axis information. In the example above, after the symbol is mirrored, its pads will still be on the TOP layer.
Both types of mirroring are useful in different circumstances. Make sure to use the correct mirror type for your particular application.
